    <note>Li(2) Duanyi [3543] Ouyang Xiu, WJ, 32.6b-8b. Han Yuanji has son, and grandfather-in-law of Han(1) Qiu [632] (q.v.), as Yue, but no such son listed in funerary inscription although all have radical 149 as generational indicator. The closest, assuming a copy error, would be son #1, Shen(2) [16824], which is the one I use. Duanyi was given a military title at age 7 and entered as an attendant in the Eastern Palace of Zhenzong. Apparently the practice of granting a military title at the time a mingzi was given was extended to include close affinal kin of the imperial family and may have been a common practive among military officers in general. Duanyi was allowed to go to and from the palace as if he were a family member (jiaren). CBD, 2, 1048-9.</note>
